PHILADELPHIA (AP) _ Carpenter Technology Corp. (CRS) on Thursday reported a loss of $7.5 million in its fiscal third quarter.
The Philadelphia-based company said it had a loss of 16 cents per share. Losses, adjusted for non-recurring gains, came to 20 cents per share.
The maker of stainless steels and special alloys posted revenue of $489 million in the period.
